Change how command objects are initialized

This change will cause the compiler to turn this:

    class SomeController {
        @Transactional
        def someAction(SomeDomain sd) {
            // application code here
        }
    }

Into this:

    class SomeController {
        def someAction() {
            someAction(null)
        }
        def someAction(SomeDomain sd) {
            withTransaction { status ->
                $tt__someAction(sd, status)
            }
        }

        def $tt_someAction(SomeDomain sd, TransactionStatus status) {
            if(sd == null) {
                sd = // initialize sd
            }
            // original application code here
        }
    }

The initialization code has been moved into the transaction handling
method and the null check is there to accommodate unit tests which
explicitly pass a parameter in to the action method.

This is related to grails/grails-data-mapping#580.

